Comment: So I heard about this movie of course. I'm not really into fantasy or into known children's tales being altered according to a screenwriter's or director's taste and style. But I came across the movie when i turned my TV on. It was a fight scene in the woods. And all I'm wondering is if this is supposed to be a parody on children's storybook tales because I feel like chuckling every few moments on how lame and predictable every bit of the fight scene seems to be.  I don't think it's supposed to be a parody though.  I think that they are actually being serious and intentional, which is sad.  And the movie really is as stupid as I thought it was.  I feel sorry for those who wasted their money seeing this movie in the theaters.

Title: Hansel and Gretel: Witch Hunters Official Trailer #1 (2012) - Jeremy Renner, Gemma Arterton Movie HD
Comment: Ha!  Hilariously bad!  Modern weapons in ... what year was this?  No explanation how they got them.  They fight with modern hand-to-hand combat techniques.  Hansel runs around in skin tight leather pants, and no one calls her out on it.  The troll kills five or six villagers and no one mentions them again, though their families were surely going hungry.  They didn't speak with accents, they used modern phraseology and modern lingo.  Hansel's repeating crossbow has a setting that makes it fire one arrow to the left and one to the right - because such a thing is so useful in situations where you are suddenly confronted with a witch on each side of you but none in front of you - which I'm sure happens about once per week.  Anyway, if such a situation just so happens, make sure the witches line up exactly right so they can both be simultaneously shot even though you're not looking at either of them.

Comment:
Honestly, i like the movie, love the idea, and ADORE the actors! :) Yes, I am pretty sure that the script could have been made better, but sometimes i just LOVED the swearing or sass that just so happened to be in the exact right places. Sure, it could be better by actually making the movie a little longer, but really, it was worth it. If you like violence and gore, this is a movie for ya ;) Don't judge a book OR movie by its cover, lol. 
Gemma Arterton (along with Jeremy Renner) is brilliant in any sense of way for me in all their movies.

Alright.
Firstly, the story: When the hell did a Blood Moon, a Hunters' Moon, have anything to do with witches? Last time I remember, a Blood Moon was used for indication that it was time for olden day villagers to hunt for food, due to the harsh cold. Not sacrifices.
And when did Witches ever make trolls their slaves and why? Trolls are stupid, oblivious, reckless, and easily avoided in the heat of a fight; they are unreliable as slaves. Witches are much more dangerous themselves.
